s new actions a=\r\nnd adds them to the pools. Also, as new people enter one&#39;s life, possibilit=\r\nies in terms of karmaphala delivery agents and sequencing may change and he=\r\nnce the pools may be re-arranged.\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; *=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=\r\n=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0 *=C3=82=C2=\r\n=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=\r\n *\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; As one engages in remedial measures such as prayers, =\r\nfasting, donations etc, one may transform one&#39;s nature, change one&#39;s vulner=\r\nabilities or re-arrange one&#39;s dynamics with other beings (including planets=\r\n, deities etc, who are the subtle agents of delivery of karmaphala, who ope=\r\nrate through other people who act as physical agents of delivery!). The kar=\r\nma pools may be re-arranged as a result. Some undesirable karmas may be dow=\r\nngraded to a lower pool or pushed down in order within the same pool. Or, s=\r\nome desirable karmas may be upgraded to a higher pool or pushed up in order=\r\n within the same pool.\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0When someone curses or blesses one, w=\r\nith sufficient mental force behind it (this is the key), the same thing can=\r\n happen. It is all about re-arranging karmas between the karmik pools. Ever=\r\ny action by one, or even people around one, has the potential to re-arrange=\r\n one&#39;s karmik pools. A karma about to give karmaphala may be postponed or a=\r\n karma that was not to give karmaphala anytime soon may be advanced sooner.=\r\n\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; However, remember that the remedial measure has to be a=\r\ns intense as the karma that it is trying to manipulate. You can move a smal=\r\nl rock with small force, but you need a large force to move a big rock or a=\r\n hill.\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; \n&gt;&gt; If there is no negative karma in one&#39;s pool t=\r\nhat can give a specific result, nobody can make one experience that result,=\r\n no matter what ritual one does. However, even great souls have a lot of ne=\r\ngative karmas in their optional pool and even evil people have a lot of pos=\r\nitive karmas in their optional pool, and hence powerful remedies, curses an=\r\nd blessings can often make some difference.\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; This point i=\r\ns well illustrated by the &quot;Guru Charitra&quot; story Digamber ji referred in his=\r\n point (3).\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; *=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=\r\n=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0 *=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=\r\n=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n If one thinks that one can escape the fruits of one&#39;s actions, one is mist=\r\nakened. God is not like us human beings, who may show favoritism towards th=\r\nose who praise them or bribe them. The He-aspect of God is a witness to the=\r\n play of actions and fruits. The She-aspect of God is the power that impart=\r\nially and impassionately manages the fine balance and order within this pla=\r\ny of actions and fruits. All beings are equal in Her eyes, from the lowest =\r\nof evil persons to the noblest of saints. She administers just and balanced=\r\n delivery of fruits to actions using available agents.\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; T=\r\nhe karmas we committed in the past are already in the pipeline and will giv=\r\ne their results sooner or later. The best we can do with them, with some ef=\r\nfort, is to perhaps reorder them somewhat. The most important thing is to n=\r\not add more serious bad karmas to the pipeline now. Simply put, selfish act=\r\nions and actions that cause pain or harm to others are bad karmas and selfl=\r\ness actions and actions that cause pleasure or benefit to others are good k=\r\narmas.\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; When it comes to manipulating the pre-existing pi=\r\npeline of karmas awaiting karmaphala, through conscious effort and current =\r\naction, yes, it is possible and general guidelines are available in shastra=\r\ns, but we can&#39;t be certain about the specific impact of each action. One th=\r\ning is for sure - remedial measure for overcoming a karma has to be commens=\r\nurate with the karma itself.\n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; You need only small force t=\r\no push a cat out of your way, but need a large force to push an elephant.\n&gt;=\r\n&gt; \n&gt;&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; Best regards,\n&gt;&gt; Narasimha\n&gt;&gt; --------\n&gt;&gt; Astrology &=\r\n Spirituality Resources: http://www.vedicastrologer.org/\n&gt;&gt; --------\n&gt;&gt; =C3=\r\n=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; \n&gt;&gt; &gt;________________________________\n&gt;&gt; &gt; From: Ajit Krishnan=\r\n \n&gt;&gt; &gt;To: mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com \n&gt;&gt; &gt;Sent: Tuesday, Februar=\r\ny 26, 2013 11:29 PM\n&gt;&gt; &gt;Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] few questions\n&gt;&gt; &gt; \n&gt;&gt; =\r\n&gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt;=C3=82=C2=A0 \n&gt;&gt; &gt;Dear=C3=82=C2=A0Digamber,\n&gt;&gt; &gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt;When a king=\r\ndom had no royal heirs, a special elephant was appointed by the courtiers t=\r\no randomly pick the next king. Thus, it was possible for a beggar to sudden=\r\nly find himself the king. Whose karma is this?=C3=82=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt;Va=\r\nsishtha gives two answers: (1) This is the karma of the ministers, king, an=\r\nd all the citizens, and (2) This is the karma of the beggar turned king.\n&gt;&gt;=\r\n &gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt;Everything is interrelated. The beggar&#39;s karma made him a king.=\r\n The elephant&#39;s karma allowed him to be the one chosen to pick the king. Th=\r\ne minister&#39;s karma allowed them to appoint the elephant to pick the king. A=\r\nnd the citizens&#39; karma allowed them to live in such a kingdom, and accept t=\r\nhe result.\n&gt;&gt; &gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt;\n&gt;&gt; &gt;The sanskrit word &quot;shaapa&qu