rmas from one&#39;s past are placed in a &quot;must experience karmaphala =\r\nin this life&quot; pool, some karmas in a &quot;preferably experience karmaphala in t=\r\nhis life&quot; pool and the rest in\n the third pool which may not be experienced=\r\n anytime soon. The way karmas are assigned and ordered in these pools is ba=\r\nsed on the balancing of karma/karmaphala sequencing of all beings.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =\r\n=C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; The assignment and ordering of these pools will consta=\r\nntly undergo churn as one engages in various new actions and adds them to t=\r\nhe pools. Also, as new people enter one&#39;s life, possibilities in terms of k=\r\narmaphala delivery agents and sequencing may change and hence the pools may=\r\n be re-arranged.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; *=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=\r\n=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp; *=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=\r\n=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp; *&lt;BR&gt;=\r\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; As one engages in remedial measures such as praye=\r\nrs, fasting, donations etc, one may transform one&#39;s nature, change one&#39;s vu=\r\nlnerabilities or re-arrange one&#39;s dynamics with other beings (including pla=\r\nnets, deities etc, who are the subtle agents of delivery of karmaphala, who=\r\n operate through\n other people who act as physical agents of delivery!). Th=\r\ne karma pools may be re-arranged as a result. Some undesirable karmas may b=\r\ne downgraded to a lower pool or pushed down in order within the same pool. =\r\nOr, some desirable karmas may be upgraded to a higher pool or pushed up in =\r\norder within the same pool.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;When someone curses or bles=\r\nses one, with sufficient mental force behind it (this is the key), the same=\r\n thing can happen. It is all about re-arranging karmas between the karmik p=\r\nools. Every action by one, or even people around one, has the potential to =\r\nre-arrange one&#39;s karmik pools. A karma about to give karmaphala may be post=\r\nponed or a karma that was not to give karmaphala anytime soon may be advanc=\r\ned sooner.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; However, remember that the remedial=\r\n measure has to be as intense as the karma that it is trying to manipulate.=\r\n You can move a small rock with small force, but you need a large force to =\r\nmove a big rock or\n a hill.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; If there =\r\nis no negative karma in one&#39;s pool that can give a specific result, nobody =\r\ncan make one experience that result, no matter what ritual one does. Howeve=\r\nr, even great souls have a lot of negative karmas in their optional pool an=\r\nd even evil people have a lot of positive karmas in their optional pool, an=\r\nd hence powerful remedies, curses and blessings can often make some differe=\r\nnce.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; This point is well illustrated by the &quot;Gu=\r\nru Charitra&quot; story Digamber ji referred in his point (3).&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nb=\r\nsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; *=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=\r\n=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp; *=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=\r\n=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp; *&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; If one =\r\nthinks that one can escape the fruits of one&#39;s actions, one is mistakened. =\r\nGod is not like us human beings, who may show favoritism towards those who =\r\npraise them or bribe them. The He-aspect of God is a witness to the play of=\r\n actions and\n fruits. The She-aspect of God is the power that impartially a=\r\nnd impassionately manages the fine balance and order within this play of ac=\r\ntions and fruits. All beings are equal in Her eyes, from the lowest of evil=\r\n persons to the noblest of saints. She administers just and balanced delive=\r\nry of fruits to actions using available agents.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt=\r\n; The karmas we committed in the past are already in the pipeline and will =\r\ngive their results sooner or later. The best we can do with them, with some=\r\n effort, is to perhaps reorder them somewhat. The most important thing is t=\r\no not add more serious bad karmas to the pipeline now. Simply put, selfish =\r\nactions and actions that cause pain or harm to others are bad karmas and se=\r\nlfless actions and actions that cause pleasure or benefit to others are goo=\r\nd karmas.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; When it comes to manipulating the pr=\r\ne-existing pipeline of karmas awaiting karmaphala, through conscious effort=\r\n and current\n action, yes, it is possible and general guidelines are availa=\r\nble in shastras, but we can&#39;t be certain about the specific impact of each =\r\naction. One thing is for sure - remedial measure for overcoming a karma has=\r\n to be commensurate with the karma itself.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; You=\r\n need only small force to push a cat out of your way, but need a large forc=\r\ne to push an elephant.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Best regards,&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;&gt; Narasimha&lt;BR&gt;&gt; --------&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Astrology &amp; Spirituality Res=\r\nources: &lt;A href=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=\r\n=3D_blank&gt;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&lt;/A&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; --------&lt;BR&gt;&gt; =C3=\r\n=82&nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;________________________________&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt=\r\n; From: Ajit Krishnan &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;To: &lt;A href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yah=\r\noogroups.com&quot; rel=3Dnofollow target=3D_blank ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom=\r\n%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&lt;/A&gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;=\r\nSent: Tuesday, February 26, 2013\n 11:29 PM&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;Subject: Re: [vedic-=\r\nwisdom] few questions&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; &lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;